{"overview":"This 87-bar fugue in A minor is anchored to its home key while executing a carefully planned tonal journey through diatonic relatives (C major, E minor, D minor) before a striking modal-mixture shift to the flat side (bVI/F major, bVII, bII) in the stretto zone, lending the climax a darkened, archaic gravity. Its most distinctive feature is the combination of compressed stretto entries with flat-side chromatic harmony in the final section, where modal mixture and expanded five-voice texture converge to intensify the concluding A minor cadence.","cross_piece_tags":["fugue","counterpoint","modal_mixture","circle_of_fifths","pedal_point","chromatic_mediant","tragic","dramatic"]}
